{"type":"message","id":"f99f854b","parentId":"8f7d39c1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:44:05.488Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The only session is the cron job itself. There are no recent user messages (within 5 minutes) from other sessions. This cron job is running in an isolated session and its only message is from this cron run itself.\n\nLet me check if there are any other sessions - I should look at the main session specifically. Let me check sessions more broadly to see if there's a main user session.\n\nActually, looking at the result, the only session is \"agent:main:cron:...\" which is this cron job itself. The \"last message\" shown is the cron job's own assistant message. This means there are no active user conversations.\n\nHowever, I need to be careful - this could be the cron job checking itself. Let me look for sessions with kind \"user\" or sessions from the feishu channel. Let me try to list all sessions without the activeMinutes filter.\n\nWait - the session key is \"agent:main:cron:3709e1d2...\" which indicates this is a cron-triggered isolated session. The `updatedAt` timestamp shows this session was just active. But the question is whether there are other user sessions.\n\nLet me check if there are any sessions from the feishu channel (which would indicate real user conversations).\n\nActually, the sessions_list with `activeMinutes: 5` and `messageLimit: 1` should show sessions active within 5 minutes. The only result is this cron job session. But I need to check if there might be a main session with姚总 that's active.\n\nLet me try a broader search - looking at all sessions without the activeMinutes filter.","thinkingSignature":"3b83c64ea86f6c52673fd918247a41235b92169b6cdec97367e5357cb81116ca"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x2x3ro1cu6my_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":10,"messageLimit":1}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":852,"o